    "phaseId": 4,
    "title": "The Passive Voice (Lebanese Style)",
    "tag": "Intermediate",
    "explanation": "Lebanese Arabic avoids the MSA internal-vowel passive. Instead, it uses two prefixes: انـ (in-) for things that happen to objects, and تـ (t-) for reflexive/process meanings. These are natural and very common in daily speech.",
